      Sets the current row to one matching the given key row, if found; otherwise the current row is set to one immediately following the given key, where following means the smallest row that compares greater than key if the direction is FORWARD, or the greatest row that compares less than key if the direction is REVERSE. If key is beyond the table range in either direction, then the contents of the current row will be undefined, and the current row number will be -1 or rowCount().

      • setRow

        public boolean setRow(ByteBuffer key)
               throws IOException
        Sets the current row to one matching the given key row, if found; otherwise the current row is set to one immediately following the given key, where following means
        • the smallest row that compares greater than key if the direction is FORWARD, or
        • the greatest row that compares less than key if the direction is REVERSE.
        If key is beyond the table range in either direction, then the contents of the current row will be undefined, and the current row number will be -1 or rowCount(). I.e. the instance will be BaseMergeSource.finished().

        The return value indicates whether the contents of the current row is well defined.

        Parameters:
        key - the look up key
        Returns:
        not BaseMergeSource.finished()
        Throws:
        IOException
